1
00:00:20,350 --> 00:00:21,390
Get in the car!

2
00:00:42,279 --> 00:00:46,709
(Episode 7, The Unbreakable Tie)

3
00:01:08,900 --> 00:01:12,439
Hwang Jung Tae,
do you not want to eat?

4
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:14,769
Pardon?

5
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:16,680
It's not that.

6
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:20,248
Why? He's eating.

7
00:01:20,249 --> 00:01:22,150
It's because he just woke up.

8
00:01:23,180 --> 00:01:25,248
It's all because
he's never had to starve...

9
00:01:25,249 --> 00:01:27,289
and gets a hot meal served to him
three times a day.

10
00:01:27,450 --> 00:01:29,796
If we just give him water
and nothing to eat for a few days,

11
00:01:29,820 --> 00:01:31,990
he'll never pick at his food again.

12
00:01:37,299 --> 00:01:39,669
Mr. Hwang,
what brings you by so early?

13
00:01:39,769 --> 00:01:43,400
Oh, I found a book
Jin A should read.

14
00:01:43,570 --> 00:01:46,108
- Here.
- My gosh, this is precious.

15
00:01:46,109 --> 00:01:48,138
("The Principles of Mathematics")

16
00:01:48,139 --> 00:01:51,179
Can she read this though?

17
00:01:51,180 --> 00:01:52,809
Yes, of course.

18
00:01:53,109 --> 00:01:56,479
She's improving by the day.

19
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:59,120
- My gosh, thank you.
- No problem.

20
00:02:00,049 --> 00:02:01,249
Oh, my.

21
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:05,759
Jin A has her midterm exam today,
so she'll come home early.

22
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:08,460
Why don't you eat with me
and wait for her?

23
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:09,829
Oh, then...

24
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,828
Then Myeong Hee should join us too.

25
00:02:12,829 --> 00:02:14,199
- Myeong Hee?
- Yes.

26
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:15,869
She's not home at the moment.

27
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:18,440
I guess her overnight shift
isn't over yet.

28
00:02:18,839 --> 00:02:20,810
- Overnight shift?
- Yes.

29
00:02:22,010 --> 00:02:23,709
She didn't work last night.

30
00:02:24,679 --> 00:02:27,209
She didn't come home last night,
so I assumed she was working.

31
00:02:27,510 --> 00:02:29,819
She didn't come home?

32
00:02:29,820 --> 00:02:30,880
No.

33
00:02:31,380 --> 00:02:33,689
Maybe she came home
after the curfew began...

34
00:02:33,690 --> 00:02:35,989
and left early this morning
before I woke up.

35
00:02:37,519 --> 00:02:39,230
After the curfew began?

36
00:02:42,530 --> 00:02:46,399
(Emergency Room)

37
00:02:55,169 --> 00:02:57,138
How can we help you?
Are you a guardian?

38
00:02:57,139 --> 00:02:58,609
No, I'm sorry.

39
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:03,279
Hey, In Young.
Can't you tidy up right away...

40
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:05,649
- Clean this up, will you?
- Yes, ma'am.

41
00:03:06,389 --> 00:03:08,959
By the way,
I thought you were off today.

42
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:12,429
Don't get me started.
This is all Myeong Hee's fault.

43
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,899
(Ethanol)

44
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:27,669
Oh, I got this. My goodness.

45
00:03:27,769 --> 00:03:28,980
In Young, right?

46
00:03:29,810 --> 00:03:32,040
- Do I know you?
- Well...

47
00:03:32,380 --> 00:03:35,619
Is Ms. Kim Myeong Hee here today?

48
00:03:36,679 --> 00:03:39,320
She didn't come in today
and didn't even call.

49
00:03:39,989 --> 00:03:42,289
She's never even taken
a half-day off,

50
00:03:42,290 --> 00:03:44,459
but she didn't even call.
I wonder what's going on.

51
00:03:46,829 --> 00:03:48,030
What?

52
00:03:49,329 --> 00:03:51,298
What do you mean Myeong Hee is gone?

53
00:03:51,299 --> 00:03:54,230
She's not at home.
She missed work without calling in.

54
00:03:54,399 --> 00:03:55,970
Did you hear from her at all?

55
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:57,839
No, I didn't.

56
00:03:58,940 --> 00:04:02,540
Maybe something urgent came up
last night.

57
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:05,950
Then she would've called
the hospital.

58
00:04:07,079 --> 00:04:08,850
Do you know where she could be?

59
00:04:08,919 --> 00:04:10,549
Why are you asking me?

60
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:13,148
Now, you know more about her
than I do.

61
00:04:13,149 --> 00:04:16,389
You've known her longer than I have.

62
00:04:16,459 --> 00:04:18,160
You said she's your best friend.

63
00:04:26,099 --> 00:04:27,229
Hello?

64
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:28,899
Hello?

65
00:04:36,279 --> 00:04:37,579
Soo Chan.

66
00:04:38,110 --> 00:04:40,180
Don't answer
Hwang Hee Tae's calls...

67
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,380
until things get sorted out.

68
00:04:42,979 --> 00:04:45,519
But if I hang up on him like that...

69
00:04:46,289 --> 00:04:47,550
Don't answer his calls.

70
00:04:58,159 --> 00:05:01,170
Do you want to keep this job or not?

71
00:05:01,370 --> 00:05:04,039
- Get your job done properly.
- I'm sorry, sir.

72
00:05:04,139 --> 00:05:06,909
Goodness, what should I do with you?

73
00:05:07,170 --> 00:05:10,440
Just do what your predecessors did.
You can't even do that?

74
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:13,050
- I'm sorry, sir.
- Excuse me.

75
00:05:13,649 --> 00:05:15,750
I'd like to report a missing person.

76
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:18,180
Oh, no. Is your child missing?

77
00:05:19,289 --> 00:05:20,518
How old?

78
00:05:20,519 --> 00:05:23,389
No, it's an adult.
She's 26 years old.

79
00:05:26,630 --> 00:05:28,329
What's your relationship with her?

80
00:05:29,899 --> 00:05:31,029
I'm her boyfriend.

81
00:05:31,930 --> 00:05:33,899
How long has she been missing?

82
00:05:34,630 --> 00:05:35,839
It's been...

83
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:38,968
About 15 hours, I think.

84
00:05:38,969 --> 00:05:41,209
15 hours?

85
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:43,779
So you saw her last night...

86
00:05:43,909 --> 00:05:45,309
but haven't heard from her since.

87
00:05:45,310 --> 00:05:46,348
That's right.

88
00:05:46,349 --> 00:05:48,310
We parted ways
in front of her place last night,

89
00:05:48,349 --> 00:05:50,019
but I can't reach her.

90
00:05:50,180 --> 00:05:52,820
- Go on. Go.
- No, wait.

91
00:05:53,820 --> 00:05:55,518
Why won't you listen to me?

92
00:05:55,519 --> 00:05:59,059
Has it ever occurred to you
that she might be avoiding you?

93
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:01,360
She's not at home,
and she didn't go to work today.

94
00:06:01,430 --> 00:06:02,999
What if she got into an accident
on the way to work...

95
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,629
Goodness. People don't go missing...

96
00:06:05,630 --> 00:06:08,398
that easily, okay?

97
00:06:08,399 --> 00:06:09,500
- Hey.
- Hello, sir.

98
00:06:11,070 --> 00:06:13,768
And we can't say she's missing
if it's only been 15 hours.

99
00:06:13,769 --> 00:06:16,139
It looks like she went somewhere.

100
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:19,549
Wait. She'd never go anywhere
without telling me.

101
00:06:19,550 --> 00:06:22,478
Come on. How do you know?

102
00:06:22,479 --> 00:06:24,820
How can you be so sure?

103
00:06:25,149 --> 00:06:27,288
Well, for example...

104
00:06:27,289 --> 00:06:28,689
Maybe she saw
her late grandparents...

105
00:06:28,690 --> 00:06:30,458
in her dream
and went to visit their graves.

106
00:06:30,459 --> 00:06:32,629
Or maybe she went to see her parents
because one of them collapsed.

107
00:06:32,630 --> 00:06:34,430
Who knows?

108
00:06:34,789 --> 00:06:35,899
Hello.

109
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:38,029
You need a haircut, punk.

110
00:06:38,829 --> 00:06:42,969
First, check all the places
where she could be.

111
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:46,809
Wait another day...
No, come back in three days.

112
00:06:46,810 --> 00:06:49,180
Then I'll open a case for you.

113
00:06:50,839 --> 00:06:52,950
I'm already so busy.

114
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:57,950
Where she could be...

115
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:00,820
Oh, I need to go to Naju.

116
00:07:01,519 --> 00:07:04,820
It's been a while since I went home.
All I did was call.

117
00:07:08,430 --> 00:07:10,599
Go away! That hurts.

118
00:07:12,769 --> 00:07:14,329
Hey, Digestive Drink!

119
00:07:14,769 --> 00:07:17,099
Your big brother is here.

120
00:07:17,870 --> 00:07:21,170
Big brother? I don't have a brother.

121
00:07:31,979 --> 00:07:33,950
I think they unplugged the phone.

122
00:07:34,190 --> 00:07:35,348
Why?

123
00:07:35,349 --> 00:07:38,060
They do it from time to time
because of my grandma.

124
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:41,190
But...

125
00:07:42,130 --> 00:07:43,700
is Myeong Hee in Naju now?

126
00:07:45,459 --> 00:07:47,598
I wanted to call them and ask,

127
00:07:47,599 --> 00:07:49,370
but you're saying
they unplugged the phone.

128
00:07:49,839 --> 00:07:52,240
Do you know
when they'll plug it back in?

129
00:07:52,909 --> 00:07:56,078
That will depend on
my grandma's condition.

130
00:07:56,079 --> 00:07:58,539
It could be for half a day?
The whole day?

131
00:07:58,979 --> 00:08:00,510
It's different each time.

132
00:08:05,050 --> 00:08:08,490
Myeong Soo,
can you give me the address?

133
00:08:08,820 --> 00:08:11,320
(190 Maeseong-ri, Sanpo-myeon,
Naju, South Jeolla Province)

134
00:08:16,399 --> 00:08:17,729
Hold on.

135
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:22,130
Visiting her parents
when it's only been a few hours...

136
00:08:25,099 --> 00:08:26,839
That's creepy.

137
00:08:27,709 --> 00:08:30,839
Okay, I'll just check from afar
and see if she's there...

138
00:08:33,479 --> 00:08:36,279
That's creepier.

139
00:08:37,780 --> 00:08:40,189
I should pick up some gifts
on the way...

140
00:08:40,190 --> 00:08:42,320
and properly introduce myself
to them...

141
00:08:42,719 --> 00:08:44,088
That will creep them out even more.

142
00:08:44,089 --> 00:08:46,089
Gosh, this is driving me crazy.

143
00:08:46,290 --> 00:08:47,329
Young man.

144
00:08:47,930 --> 00:08:49,759
Listen, can you...

145
00:08:50,099 --> 00:08:52,728
Can you call a doctor?

146
00:08:52,729 --> 00:08:53,800
What?

147
00:08:54,099 --> 00:08:58,099
My son is about to die right now.

148
00:08:58,369 --> 00:09:01,070
I took him to a local hospital...

149
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:03,838
and they said I need to prepare
to say goodbye.

150
00:09:03,839 --> 00:09:06,410
Oh, what's wrong with your son?

151
00:09:06,810 --> 00:09:07,879
Oh, my.

152
00:09:08,579 --> 00:09:10,320
Are you a doctor?

153
00:09:11,420 --> 00:09:13,089
Oh, well, no...

154
00:09:14,619 --> 00:09:15,719
I am...

155
00:09:17,020 --> 00:09:21,030
Then why don't I call
an ambulance for you?

156
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,598
Why are you up already?

157
00:09:27,599 --> 00:09:29,279
You should lie down
and get some more rest.

158
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:32,269
I'm sick of lying down.

159
00:09:32,270 --> 00:09:33,640
It's just a cold.

160
00:09:33,839 --> 00:09:37,008
Gosh, you must be fine now,
hearing you say that.

161
00:09:37,009 --> 00:09:39,079
- Drink this.
- Okay.

162
00:09:46,219 --> 00:09:47,449
Where's Mother?

163
00:09:47,450 --> 00:09:49,159
She got up
in the middle of the night...

164
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:50,989
and stayed by your bedside...

165
00:09:53,190 --> 00:09:54,290
She's not in the room.

166
00:09:55,589 --> 00:09:57,128
She was here just a minute ago.

167
00:09:57,129 --> 00:09:58,628
My goodness.

168
00:09:58,629 --> 00:10:00,399
Gosh, I was busy brewing
your herbal tonic.

169
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:02,738
I'll go take a look around
the neighborhood...

170
00:10:02,739 --> 00:10:05,098
so call the village foreman
and ask him to make an announcement.

171
00:10:05,099 --> 00:10:07,310
Okay. Where's the phone?

172
00:10:09,540 --> 00:10:10,680
I can't believe this.

173
00:10:11,109 --> 00:10:12,180
Is anyone home?

174
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:15,708
- Hyun Chul.
- Gosh, Mother!

175
00:10:15,709 --> 00:10:17,578
- Mother!
- Goodness.

176
00:10:17,579 --> 00:10:18,848
Where have you been?

177
00:10:18,849 --> 00:10:20,920
You scared me to death.

178
00:10:21,349 --> 00:10:22,660
Where is her son?

179
00:10:23,890 --> 00:10:24,959
Oh, yes.

180
00:10:25,459 --> 00:10:27,030
I'm her son.

181
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:33,329
Oh, she said you were my age.

182
00:10:33,670 --> 00:10:35,110
Can you tell me
what's troubling you?

183
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:38,039
Sorry?

184
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:41,440
Oh, did she say her son was
about to die...

185
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:42,909
and drag you here?

186
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:45,539
The thing is, my mother loses
her memory from time to time.

187
00:10:45,540 --> 00:10:47,878
Gosh, I'm sorry about this.

188
00:10:47,879 --> 00:10:49,749
Oh, don't worry about it.

189
00:10:49,950 --> 00:10:51,550
I'm glad you're okay.

190
00:10:53,150 --> 00:10:54,150
Then...

191
00:10:54,151 --> 00:10:56,488
- Thank you.
- Have a good day.

192
00:10:56,489 --> 00:10:57,789
Mother, let's go inside.

193
00:10:57,790 --> 00:11:00,089
Oh, by the way...

194
00:11:01,259 --> 00:11:03,059
Can you tell me which direction
this is?

195
00:11:03,060 --> 00:11:04,759
- It's my first time here.
- Oh, sure.

196
00:11:05,859 --> 00:11:08,179
(190 Maeseong-ri, Sanpo-myeon,
Naju, South Jeolla Province)

197
00:11:22,050 --> 00:11:23,919
Sorry we don't have
many side dishes.

198
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,950
I should've fried some eggs.

199
00:11:34,329 --> 00:11:35,689
I'm sorry you came
all the way here...

200
00:11:35,690 --> 00:11:37,560
but couldn't meet Myeong Hee.

201
00:11:38,459 --> 00:11:41,728
Seeing you're here on a weekday
instead of at work,

202
00:11:41,729 --> 00:11:43,540
I guess you're a college student.

203
00:11:44,599 --> 00:11:47,910
Well, yes... So...

204
00:11:48,709 --> 00:11:51,608
I'm about to graduate
from college soon.

205
00:11:51,609 --> 00:11:54,810
You're the same age as Myeong Hee
but haven't graduated yet?

206
00:11:55,879 --> 00:11:57,619
You must've taken a few years off.

207
00:11:58,050 --> 00:12:01,820
Actually, I didn't take time off...

208
00:12:04,219 --> 00:12:06,358
It takes six years to graduate
from my department.

209
00:12:06,359 --> 00:12:07,390
Six years?

210
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:11,200
Then does that mean...

211
00:12:11,599 --> 00:12:14,070
you're a medical student?

212
00:12:14,229 --> 00:12:16,140
Where? Chonnam National University?

213
00:12:16,739 --> 00:12:17,800
Chosun University?

214
00:12:18,369 --> 00:12:20,009
No. It's...

215
00:12:20,969 --> 00:12:22,040
Don't tell me...

216
00:12:22,709 --> 00:12:23,749
Seoul National University?

217
00:12:26,050 --> 00:12:27,050
Yes.

218
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:31,020
Cut it out.

219
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:36,089
Mother, what are you smiling about?

220
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:42,729
So, do your parents know...

221
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:45,359
that you're seeing Myeong Hee?

222
00:12:46,229 --> 00:12:49,400
Why are you asking that?
How silly of you.

223
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:51,868
Kids these days
aren't like us anymore.

224
00:12:51,869 --> 00:12:53,409
Don't mind him and eat.

225
00:12:53,410 --> 00:12:55,169
Sorry he keeps interrupting
your meal.

226
00:12:55,170 --> 00:12:56,410
Go on.

227
00:12:56,810 --> 00:12:58,609
- Go on and eat.
- Okay.

228
00:12:59,379 --> 00:13:01,079
Stop talking to him
when he's eating.

229
00:13:05,749 --> 00:13:07,118
Thank you so much for today.

230
00:13:07,119 --> 00:13:09,150
I came so abruptly,
but you even cooked for me.

231
00:13:09,959 --> 00:13:12,729
Gosh, I'm sorry I couldn't make you
a proper meal.

232
00:13:13,359 --> 00:13:14,728
If you tell me in advance next time,

233
00:13:14,729 --> 00:13:16,958
I'll show you how good a cook I am.

234
00:13:16,959 --> 00:13:18,729
So come with Myeong Hee
next time, okay?

235
00:13:20,670 --> 00:13:23,499
Okay. I look forward
to seeing you again.

236
00:13:24,599 --> 00:13:26,810
Ma'am, I'll see you next time.

237
00:13:39,050 --> 00:13:41,290
We should repair this darn door.

238
00:13:41,450 --> 00:13:42,650
Take care!

239
00:13:50,729 --> 00:13:53,070
She's not here either.
Where on earth is she?

240
00:13:57,839 --> 00:14:00,709
No, it'll be okay.
Her mom told me not to worry.

241
00:14:02,070 --> 00:14:04,940
She'll be fine. I'm sure she's fine.

242
00:14:09,780 --> 00:14:10,849
Myeong Hee!

243
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:19,320
Where did you go
without even telling me?

244
00:14:19,660 --> 00:14:20,729
Do you know how...

245
00:14:23,530 --> 00:14:25,560
Do you know what I was thinking?

246
00:14:26,030 --> 00:14:27,930
What brings you here?

247
00:14:29,099 --> 00:14:31,019
Do you think I came all the way here
to have fun?

248
00:14:31,599 --> 00:14:33,139
You weren't at home or at work...

249
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:34,620
so I thought
you might've come here...

250
00:14:39,140 --> 00:14:41,348
I know it may creep you out. I know,

251
00:14:41,349 --> 00:14:43,019
but put yourself in my shoes.

252
00:14:43,020 --> 00:14:44,020
How could I remain calm...

253
00:14:44,021 --> 00:14:45,619
How did you find out my address?

254
00:14:48,089 --> 00:14:49,560
I asked Myeong Soo.

255
00:14:51,619 --> 00:14:53,430
I know this may creep you out too.

256
00:14:53,629 --> 00:14:54,890
I know, but...

257
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:03,270
Myeong Hee, what's wrong?

258
00:15:07,109 --> 00:15:08,109
Is something wrong?

259
00:15:12,579 --> 00:15:14,050
What's wrong, Myeong Hee?

260
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:17,840
You seem like a different person.

261
00:15:22,290 --> 00:15:23,290
Myeong Hee.

262
00:15:44,009 --> 00:15:45,839
Stay still, you brat.

263
00:15:59,560 --> 00:16:01,030
Who are you people?

264
00:16:01,890 --> 00:16:03,628
